{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}} '''Cornelia James''' is a firm of British [[glove]]makers, founded in 1946, and with a [[Royal Warrant of Appointment (United Kingdom)|Royal Warrant]] since 1979.
==History== {{see also|Cornelia James (glovemaker)}} [[Cornelia James (glovemaker)|Cornelia Katz]] was born in Vienna in 1917, and left in 1939 via Paris to London to try to get a United States visa, but met Jack James and married him six weeks later in 1940.<ref>{{cite news|author=Gwen Stapleton |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/obituary-cornelia-james-1133698.html |title=Obituary: Cornelia James &#124; Culture |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |date= |accessdate=18 January 2016}}</ref> She was a Jewish refugee and set up business in London in 1946 making gloves. In 1947, [[Norman Hartnell]] asked her to make the "going-away" gloves for the then Princess Elizabeth after her marriage to Prince Phillip.<ref name="cjcom about">{{cite web|url=http://www.corneliajames.com/pages/about-us |title=Cornelia James, About Us |website=Corneliajames.com |date= |accessdate=18 January 2016}}</ref>
In the 1950s, the company had 250 employees in a former dairy in Brighton.<ref name="nytimes handson">Susan Fowler, [https://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/24/style/international/cornelia-james-a-glove-maker-to-the-queen.html Gloves Fit for a Queen, With Hands-On Craftsmanship], ''Nytimes.com'', 23 November 2014</ref>
==Activities== Cornelia James has been [[Royal Warrant of Appointment (United Kingdom)|Royal Warrant]] holders since 1979, and is now based in [[Lewes]], Sussex.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.royalwarrant.org/company/cornelia-james-ltd |title=Cornelia James Ltd &#124; Royal Warrant Holders Association |website=Royalwarrant.org |date= |accessdate=18 January 2016}}</ref>
The company is now run by her daughter, Genevieve James, who's also the brand's creative director.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.corneliajames.com/pages/about-us |title=Cornelia James, About Us |publisher=Corneliajames.com |date= |accessdate=18 January 2016}}</ref> Notable clients include the Duchess of Cambridge, Princess Anne, Rihanna, Taylor Swift and Madonna.<ref name="cjcom about"/>
Cornelia James produces high-end products for wealthy individuals. A pair of full-length pure-wool gloves cuffed with silver fox fur cost $570. [[Japan]] is the company's best customer.<ref name="nytimes handson"/>
