{{Orphan|date=June 2016}}
In [[music]], an '''interdominant''' is a '''temporary dominant''', the [[dominant (music)|dominant]] of a [[key (music)|key]] other than the [[tonic (music)|tonic]].<ref>Blom, Eric (2008). ''Dictionary of Music'', p.263. {{ISBN|1-4437-3452-7}}.</ref> Since a composition [[common practice period|generally]] begins and ends with the tonic, the dominant of notes other than the tonic would be found in the middle.
