[[Image:Edificioconsejoculturavalparaiso.jpg|200px|right]] The '''National Council of Culture and the Arts''' ('''CNCA''') was the [[Chile]]an government agency responsible for arts and cultural policy. The Council was founded in 2003 and amalgamated arts and cultural policy under a single agency.<ref>[http://www.consejodelacultura.cl/portal/galeria/text/text106.pdf Ley del Consejo Nacional de la Cultura y las Artes] (Spanish)</ref> It was a cabinet-level position in the Chilean position. Since the Council was founded, six ministers have been in charge of the Council: [[José Weinstein]] under President [[Ricardo Lagos Escobar]], [[Paulina Urrutia]] under President [[Michelle Bachelet]], [[Luciano Cruz-Coke]] and [[Roberto Ampuero]] under President [[Sebastián Piñera]], Claudia Barattini and [[Ernesto Ottone]] under the second period of President Michelle Bachelet.
Since 2004, CNCA has awarded the [[Pablo Neruda Order of Artistic and Cultural Merit]] to international figures who have stood out for contributions made in the field of art and culture,<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.elmostrador.cl/cultura/2007/12/01/otorgan-a-musico-cubano-leo-brouwer-la-orden-al-merito-pablo-neruda/?php%20bloginfo(%27url%27);%20?%3E/cultura |title=Otorgan a músico cubano Leo Brouwer la Orden al Mérito Pablo Neruda |trans-title=Cuban Musician Leo Brouwer Awarded the Pablo Neruda Order of Merit |work=[[El Mostrador]] |language=Spanish |date=1 December 2007 |access-date=11 January 2018}}</ref> as well as the [[Pablo Neruda Ibero-American Poetry Award]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.laestafetadelviento.es/actualidad/noticias/ganador-del-premio-iberoamericano-de-poesia-pablo-neruda |title=Ganador del Premio Iberoamericano de Poesía Pablo Neruda |trans-title=Winner of the Pablo Neruda Ibero-American Poetry Award |work=La Estefeta del Viento |language=Spanish |date=24 January 2012 |access-date=29 January 2018}}</ref> Since 2006, as a result of Law No. 19.981, CNCA has given the [[Pedro Sienna Awards]] for Chilean audiovisual production.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.emol.com/noticias/magazine/2006/01/14/207835/cine-nuevos-premios-pedro-sienna-entregaron-sus-primeros-nominados.html |title=Cine: Nuevos premios Pedro Sienna entregaron sus primeros nominados |trans-title=Film: New Pedro Sienna Awards Announce Their First Nominees |work=[[El Mercurio]] |location=Santiago |language=Spanish |date=14 January 2006 |access-date=12 January 2018}}</ref>
The National Council of Culture and the Arts was replaced with the [[Ministry of Culture, the Arts and Patrimony]].
