'''Tritik''' stitching is a small running line of [[Stitch (textile arts)|stitching]] that is gathered tightly. It is often used in [[African textiles]] and the designs are much bolder than in most other forms of stitching. This type of stitching is mostly found in Africa. It also played an important role in [[tie-dye]]ing.

